    edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Sendable

    public class SimpleCommand
extends edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.InstantCommand
    A simple way to construct an InstantCommand.

    To create a SimpleCommand easily, simply pass it a no-argument lambda containing the code you would like to execute. For example, to create a InstantCommand that requires the Robot.shifter Subsystem, simply write: 

       Command shift = new SimpleCommand(() -> Robot.shifter.shift(), Robot.shifter);
    Multiple Subystems can be added onto the end of the constructor to add multiple requirements.

    This can be used to quickly and easily put a button on the SmartDashboard/Shuffleboard to run some code. Use SmartDashboard.putData(Sendable) to pass it a newly created instance of this class.
